The double of 1NT in modern competitive bidding usually is used as a form of takeout. Therefore, it should be ignored as it does not use up any bidding space. The partnership can continue to use transfers and Stayman. Further, another bid become available after the double of 1NT. That is redouble where the responder can show a hand with 8 points or more which may not be suitable for either Stayman or transfer - see next example.|
pg| ***** 167 ***** |


