NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|But on this example, South would still like to play 3N but does not have a spade stopper. Therefore he cue bids 3S, which denies a spade stopper, and asks North to bid 3N with a stopper. Further, he may consider 4H bid and risk a 5-2 trump as he has the top two trumps. This is no different than many auctions where the opponent has overcalled and someone cue bids the overcalled suit to ask partner for a stopper (sometimes called a "Western cue bid").|
